"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-paris-olympics-2024-day-twoschedule-highlights-team-gb-events-how-watch-b1173154.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  TheParis Olympicsare fully underway after an action-packed first full day.  Here's the best of the action for day two,with the full schedule across the games available here.  10.40am: Women's gymnastics qualifying  Paris will get its first look at Simone Biles, as the American superstar joins her team-mates in the all-important qualifying session at the Bercy Arena, which will determine who goes for gold in each of the team and individual finals later in the programme. Britain go in the earlier sub-division from 8.30am.  4.45pm: Women's canoe slalom K1  On to the waters of the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium, where Kimberley Woods will be looking to put the disappointment of a 10th-placed finish at Tokyo behind her, though the 28-year-old's best hope for gold may come later in the fortnight, in the chaotic kayak cross discipline, where she is the reigning world champion.  Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Great gifts, foodie delights and experiences for the festive season  4.49pm: Judo, women's -52kg class  It could be a busy half-hour. Chelsie Giles, the Tokyo bronze medalist, is Team GB 's big hope on the judo mat, and provided she comes through the morning qualifying rounds, will be targeting another medal on Sunday afternoon.  8.44pm: Men's 100m breaststroke final  If Britain are not on the medal table come half-past eight on Sunday evening, then they surely will be by 9pm. But what colour will it be?  Adam Peaty is looking to retain the crown he won in both Rio and Tokyo, despite a tumultuous three years in and out of the sport since the last Games. His rivalry with China's Qin Haiyang is set to come to a head at La Defense Arena, with just a quarter of a second between their best times this year.  08.30:Shooting- men's 10m air pistol final  11.00:Shooting- women's 10m air pistol final  13.10:Cycling (mountain biking)- women's cross country  15.00:Judo- men's 66kg final and women's 52kg final  16.00:Skateboarding- women's street final  16.11:Archery- women's team gold medal match  16.45:Canoe slalom- women's kayak single final  19.30:Swimming- men's 400m individual medley final  19.40:Swimming- women's 100m butterfly final  20.44:Swimming- men's 100m breaststroke final  20.45:Fencing- women's foil individual gold medal bout  21.15:Fencing- men's \\u00e9p\\u00e9e individual gold medal bout  TV channel:The BBC has announced it will broadcast two live streams of the action from July 27 to August 11 - for the duration of the Games.\\u00a0This will be on BBC One, BBC Two or a stream available by clicking the red button on Freeview or a smart TV.  There is reduced coverage compared with previous years, however, when BBC broadcasted everything from archery to wrestling live on its website or channels. Instead, Discovery+ is the rights holder for Paris 2024 and is showing every moment across Eurosport channels in the UK from 7am-10.30pm every day.  Live stream:Fans can also catch the BBC coverage live online for free via the BBC Sport website and BBC iPlayer. The Discovery+ app will be showing extensive coverage, which begins at a monthly fee of \\u00a33.99.  Highlights:The BBC will be showing a nightly highlights show called Today at the Games.  Live blog:You can follow all the action viaStandard Sport'slive blog, with expert analysis from reporters Matt Majendie and Malik Ouzia in Paris.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"